Defendant in custody.
On count 1, bail jumping, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of four (4) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by two (2) years extended supervision, concurrent with all sentences imposed on 14 CF 97, 14 CF 156, 14 CF 157 and concurrent with the sentence presently being served in Kewaunee County.
On count 2, misdemeanor theft, the defendant is sentenced to nine (9) month incarceration, concurrent with count 1 of this case and concurrent with all sentences imposed on 14 CF 97, 14 CF 156, 14 CF 157 and with the sentence presently being served in Kewaunee County.
The defendant has credit for 8 days on this case.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Programs.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Maintain fulltime employment;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) maintain absolute sobriety;
7) pay restitution of $6.20 to Terry Preston.
The $750.00 cash bail from this case is to be forwarded to the Department of Corrections and be disbursed for restitution. (check instruction no: CR 27)
